article.headline: Central Florida 64, East Carolina 59
article.story: GREENVILLE, N.C. (AP) -- Justin Rose scored 18 points to lead UCF to a 64-59 victory over East Carolina in a Conference USA game Wednesday night. Anthony Williams scored 14 points for UCF (9-8, 3-1 Conference USA). Corey Rouse led the Pirates (6-12, 0-5) with 22 points and 12 rebounds. Josh King had 10 points. UCF led 37-30 at halftime, and its largest lead was 10 points with 14:48 left in the second half. The Pirates' largest lead -- 2 points -- came with 12:36 left in the first half.
